Step 1: Identify the key numbers from the balance sheet.
• Initial Total Assets on 2023-12-31 = 13,000,000.00 
• Ending Total Assets on 2024-02-05 = 14,890,758.71

Step 2: Calculate the average total assets.
 Average Total Assets = (Initial Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2 
  = (13,000,000.00 + 14,890,758.71) / 2 
  = 27,890,758.71 / 2 
  ≈ 13,945,379.36

Step 3: Identify the Total Revenue from the income statement.
• Total Revenue = 3,956,433.90

Step 4: Calculate the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.
 Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets 
  = 3,956,433.90 / 13,945,379.36 
  ≈ 0.2839

Step 5: Present the ratio rounded (as in the example, we round to two decimal places or one).
Rounding to two decimal places gives approximately 0.28.

Thus, the final solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.28"
  }
}
